====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}

# A tree of the orange family ({{taxlink|Citrus × limon|nothospecies|noshow=1|ver=161014}}, syn. {{taxlink|Citrus bergamia|species|noshow=1|ver=161014}}), having a roundish or pear-shaped fruit, from the rind of which an essential oil of delicious odor is extracted, much prized as a perfume. Also, the fruit.
# The essence or perfume made from the fruit.
#: {{rfquotek|Johnson}}
# A variety of snuff perfumed with bergamot.
#* {{rfdate|and other bibliographic particulars}} {{w|William Cowper}}
#*: ''The better hand {{...}} gives the nose its '''bergamot'''.''
# Either of two plants of the mint family noted for their bergamot-like scent:
## {{taxlink|Mentha × piperita|nothospecies|noshow=1|ver=161014}}, [[nothosubspecies]] ''citrata'', more commonly known as {{vern|bergamot mint}}
## ''[[Monarda didyma]]'', also known as {{vern|American bergamot}} or [[bee balm]].
# A variety of pear.
#: {{rfquotek|Johnson}}

